{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Command segmentation treats newline-separated statements as separate segments, not one monolithic block.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The failure boundary is command-text segmentation logic itself. This can be reproduced by calling the segmenter/parser function with a multiline shell string; no filesystem, subprocess, or cross-module wiring is strictly required.","test_description":"Call the segmentation function with input like `FOO=1\\nBAR=2\\ngh pr create --fill` and assert it returns separate executable segments/statements (with `gh pr create ...` isolated as its own segment) rather than one `not_a_trigger` monolith.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.85,"Integration":0.13,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A multi-line shell block with variable assignments followed by `gh pr create` is recognized as a PR-create trigger.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The incident came from interaction between segmentation and trigger classification. A unit test of either function alone can miss this boundary bug; wiring both modules together is the minimum to catch the real regression.","test_description":"Run the PostToolUse classification pipeline end-to-end in-process (segmenter + trigger detector) on a multiline block: assignments on earlier lines and `gh pr create` on the final line. Assert final classification is `pr_create_trigger` (not `not_a_trigger`).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A similar multi-line block that ends with `gh issue create` is not incorrectly treated as a PR-create trigger.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a boundary correctness check on the same multi-module pipeline (segmentation + trigger-type classification), specifically preventing false positives across closely related commands.","test_description":"Execute the same in-process PostToolUse pipeline with multiline assignments plus terminal command `gh issue create ...`. Assert classification is non-PR trigger (e.g., `not_a_trigger` or `issue_create_trigger`) and no PR-review loop start signal is produced.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When a PR-create trigger is detected, the hook can reconstruct and persist the PR identifier needed by the review loop state.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior crosses detection, identifier extraction/reconstruction, and filesystem persistence. Local filesystem I/O is enough; real `gh` subprocess/network is not required if the event payload/output fixture carries the needed data.","test_description":"Feed a PR-create trigger event fixture into PostToolUse with a temp state directory. Assert the persisted state file contains the expected reconstructed PR identifier fields (e.g., repo + PR number/URL) and survives a fresh read from disk.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"After PR-create detection, the review gate state is written in a form that the pre-tool enforcement hook can read and enforce.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real boundary is cross-hook contract compatibility (writer/reader schema + enforcement logic) via local state storage. This is best caught by wiring both hooks against the same temp state path.","test_description":"Invoke PostToolUse to write gate state after a PR-create trigger, then invoke PreToolUse with a command that should be blocked without review completion. Assert PreToolUse reads the written state and enforces blocking/allow rules correctly.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
